    "entry_4": "Trained at Harvard, Cornell, and Stanford — followed by 2M+ across digital platforms",
    "bio_paragraph": "Dr. Khaled Ghattass is a cell biologist and expert in human behavior who has woven science and art together over a 15-year journey of observing human behavior and influencing communities. As an executive storyteller and poet, Dr. Ghattass works to restore balance to our societies by confronting the misconceptions that negatively shape individuals, families, and communities across the Arab world. Through a distinctive narrative approach, he weaves together science, art, and philosophy to deliver content that fosters critical thinking and calls for positive change. As the founder of the social initiative \"Al-Warsheh\" in Lebanon, Dr. Ghattass empowers balanced young leaders through art, culture, and science.",
